      <h1 class='title'>Workforce Development</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 14 November 2002 vol 394 cc2-3WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_2ws' title='Col. 2WS &mdash; HC Deb 14 November 2002 vol 394 c2WS' name='column_2ws' href='#column_2ws' rel='bookmark'>2WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0394P0_20021114_CWS_7'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-douglas-alexander' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0394P0_20021114_CWS_7' title='Link to this speech by Mr Douglas Alexander' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-douglas-alexander" title="Mr Douglas Alexander">The Minister of State (Mr. Douglas Alexander)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Strategy Unit's report "In Demand, Adult Skills in the 21<sup>st</sup> Century&#x2014;part 2" has today been published as a report of the Government.</p><p>The report, commissioned by the Prime Minister, sets out a detailed and long-term plan for improving the productivity of the UK through raising skills levels in the workforce.</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_3ws' title='Col. 3WS &mdash; HC Deb 14 November 2002 vol 394 c3WS' name='column_3ws' href='#column_3ws' rel='bookmark'>3WS</a><p>It focuses on the government's strategy for
          <q>Raising demand from employers and individuals, providing access to good quality information and advice and supporting those who find it the most difficult to access development to meet their needs, particularly small businesses and individuals with lower skill levels.</q>
          
          <q>Improving the quality and responsiveness of training to make sure it meets the needs of employers and individuals.</q>
          <q>Providing a government framework of qualifications and accountabilities that supports development to support higher productivity and keep pace with industrial change.</q></p><p>The report also sets out who is responsible for delivering the improvements, how progress will be monitored and how success will be evaluated.</p><p>Copies of the report have been placed in the libraries of the House. Additional copies and further information can also be found on the Cabinet Office website at <a class='resolved-url' href="http://www.cabinet-office.gov.uk/inn">www.cabinet-office. gov.uk/inn</a> ovation.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
